<HEADLINE>
PRESIDENT ANNOUNCES MINI-LINKS FOR PENGHU
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  March 31 (CNA) 03/31/07  20:54:06 (By Flor Wang)
</P>
<P>
President Chen Shui-bian announced in Penghu Saturday that from
April 1, residents on the outlying island are eligible to use the
"mini three links" via the islands of Kinmen and Matsu to travel
direct to China.
</P>
<P>
Chen made the announcement during an inspection tour of Penghu
Island.
</P>
<P>
Stating that the central government is very concerned about
economic development in the outlying islands, Chen said that the
relevant government  authorities are always keen on providing
incentives to help local development.
</P>
<P>
From Sunday, Penghu residents will be able to sail to China via
Kinmen and Matsu islands, which have since January 2001
maintained direct ferry services with Xiamen and Mawei ports in
Fujian Province that lies opposite on the other side of the
Taiwan Strait.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Chinese tourists will also be permitted to
proceed to Penghu via Kinmen or Matsu aboard ferries or planes on
a case-by-case basis, he added.
</P>
<P>
While in Penghu, the president also paid a visit to Marjorie I.
Bly, an 88-year- old public health nurse from the United States,
who has served leper patients there for more than 40 years.
</P>
<P>
Chen bestowed a state medal to Bly in recognition of her long-
term contributions and the sacrifices she has made to the people
of Penghu.
</P>
